<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Daily Movement Digest — {{ tick_date }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Watchlist Monitoring · 24-Hour Window</div>
    <h1>Daily Movement<br/>Digest</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Material on-chain activity observed across {{ total_watched }}
      monitored wallets during the past tick. {{ material_count }}
      wallet{{ 's' if material_count != 1 else '' }} crossed a
      materiality threshold and warrant{{ '' if material_count != 1 else 's' }}
      operator review.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Tick Window</dt>
      <dd>{{ tick_window }}<span class="secondary">{{ tick_duration }} wallclock</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Wallets Snapshotted</dt>
      <dd>{{ snapshotted }}<span class="secondary">of {{ total_watched }} active watchlist rows</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Material Changes</dt>
      <dd>{{ material_count }}<span class="secondary">{{ freezeable_count }} on freezeable wallets</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Total Outflow Observed</dt>
      <dd>USD {{ total_outflow_usd }}<span class="secondary">net negative balance changes</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Digest Identifier</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ digest_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Errors</dt>
      <dd>{{ error_count }}<span class="secondary">per-wallet snapshot failures</span></dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

{% if material_count == 0 %}
<div class="summary-box">
  <p style="margin:0">
    <strong>No material movement observed.</strong>
    All {{ snapshotted }} watched wallets are within materiality
    thresholds since the last snapshot. No operator action is
    required from this tick. The next tick will run on the standard
    nightly schedule; an interim manual tick can be requested via
    <span class="mono">recupero-worker --watch-tick</span>.
  </p>
</div>
{% else %}

<div class="summary-box urgent">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;">
    <strong>Action recommended.</strong>
    {{ material_count }} watched wallet{{ 's have' if material_count != 1 else ' has' }}
    moved funds, received new transfers, or changed balance beyond
    the materiality threshold in the past 24 hours. The summary
    below identifies each affected wallet, the magnitude of the
    change, and the on-chain reference for verification.
  </p>
  {% if freezeable_count > 0 %}
  <p style="margin:0;">
    Of these, <strong>{{ freezeable_count }}</strong> are flagged as
    freezeable through an asset issuer. Any new outbound transfer
    from a freezeable wallet is grounds to expedite the existing
    issuer freeze request — recommend immediate follow-up to the
    relevant issuer compliance contact{{ 's' if freezeable_count != 1 else '' }}.
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</div>

<h2>1. Material Changes Observed</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Wallet</th>
    <th>Role</th>
    <th>Issuer</th>
    <th>Δ Balance (USD)</th>
    <th>New Tx</th>
    <th>Last Snapshot</th>
  </tr>
  {% for c in changes %}
  <tr class="{{ c.row_class }}">
    <td class="mono">{% if c.explorer_url %}<a href="{{ c.explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ c.address_short }}</a>{% else %}{{ c.address_short }}{% endif %}</td>
    <td>{{ c.role }}{% if c.label_name %}<br/><span class="small secondary">{{ c.label_name }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
    <td>{{ c.issuer or '—' }}{% if c.asset_symbol %}<br/><span class="small secondary">{{ c.asset_symbol }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
    <td class="amount">{{ c.delta_usd_human }}</td>
    <td class="amount">{{ c.tx_count_delta_human }}</td>
    <td class="mono small">{{ c.prior_taken_at_human }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>

<h2>2. Recommended Operator Actions</h2>
<ol>
  {% if freezeable_count > 0 %}
  <li>
    For freezeable wallets with new outbound activity
    ({{ freezeable_count }} above): notify the relevant issuer
    compliance contact{{ 's' if freezeable_count != 1 else '' }}
    of the new transfer{{ 's' if freezeable_count != 1 else '' }} and
    request expedited review of the standing freeze request. The
    original freeze brief{{ 's' if freezeable_count != 1 else '' }}
    accompanies this digest by case reference.
  </li>
  {% endif %}
  <li>
    Cross-reference any large outbound transfers against the
    perpetrator's known on-chain pattern before sending fresh
    process — sudden, unusual movement is often the perpetrator
    reacting to investigative pressure and identifies their next
    wallet of interest, which can be added to the watchlist.
  </li>
  <li>
    For wallets where the change is balance-only (no new tx — e.g.
    inbound consolidation from another address): no immediate action
    required, but the wallet's continued activity confirms the
    perpetrator's operational behavior, which strengthens the case
    narrative for the LE handoff.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>3. Per-Wallet Detail</h2>
{% for c in changes %}
<div class="summary-box {{ 'urgent' if c.is_freezeable else '' }}">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;">
    <strong>{{ c.address_short }}</strong>
    {% if c.label_name %}({{ c.label_name }}){% endif %}
    — <em>{{ c.reason }}</em>
  </p>
  <table class="evidence" style="margin:0;">
    <tr><th>Address</th><td class="mono">{% if c.explorer_url %}<a href="{{ c.explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ c.address }}</a>{% else %}{{ c.address }}{% endif %}</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Chain</th><td>{{ c.chain }}</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Role on case</th><td>{{ c.role }}</td></tr>
    {% if c.issuer %}<tr><th>Asset issuer</th><td>{{ c.issuer }}{% if c.asset_symbol %} ({{ c.asset_symbol }}){% endif %}</td></tr>{% endif %}
    <tr><th>Prior snapshot</th><td class="mono">{{ c.prior_taken_at_human }} — USD {{ c.prior_usd_human }}, {{ c.prior_tx_count_human }} txs</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Current snapshot</th><td class="mono">{{ c.new_taken_at_human }} — USD {{ c.new_usd_human }}, {{ c.new_tx_count_human }} txs</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Net change</th><td class="amount">{{ c.delta_usd_human }} · {{ c.tx_count_delta_human }} new tx</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}

<h2>{{ '4' if material_count > 0 else '1' }}. Verification</h2>
<p>
  Every snapshot in this digest is sourced from public on-chain state
  fetched between {{ tick_started_human }} and {{ tick_finished_human }} UTC.
  Each address links to its block-explorer record. The watchlist itself
  is populated automatically from the worker's freeze stage; manual
  additions (via <span class="mono">scripts/recupero_watch.py</span>) are
  marked with <span class="mono">flagged_by</span> set to the operator's
  identifier.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Source: Etherscan API v2 (multichain); CoinGecko historical pricing
  (cached); our internal watchlist database. Snapshot history is
  retained indefinitely in <span class="mono">public.watchlist_snapshots</span>
  for audit purposes.
</p>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ digest_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Strictly Confidential.</span> Distributed to subscribed operators only.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
